The International Football Federation will pick its player of the
year and the Special Player of the Century award that pits Argentine
hero Diego Maradona against Brazilian legend Pele. The top
candidates for this year's player of the year are Real Madrid's
Louis Fego, who moved from Barcelona in the most expensive transfer
in the game's history. Also nominated, Revaldo of Brazil and French
hero Zenedine Zidane. Zidane led France to the European title this
year after helping France win the World Cup title two years ago.
There are 27 nominees for the player of the century award, but
Maradona and Pele are the favorites. Pele led Brazil to three World
Cup titles and scored more that 1200 goals. He has been named the
'athlete of the century' in a survey of National Olympic Committees.
